# Sequence diagram: OIDC (Authorization Code + PKCE) login for a SPA, with an
# API-gateway JWT check and a fine-grained authorization check.
#
# Sequence diagrams ignore the layout engine, so readability here comes from
# concise, \n-wrapped message labels (see SKILL.md "Readability"). d2 masks the
# lifelines behind labels so lines don't strike through text in its native export.

shape: sequence_diagram

browser: Browser (SPA)
idp: Identity Provider
apim: API Gateway
api: API Service
authz: Authorization (AuthZed/SpiceDB)

browser -> idp: 1. /authorize\n(PKCE challenge)
idp -> browser: 2. Login + MFA prompt
browser -> idp: 3. Credentials
idp -> browser: 4. Auth code
browser -> idp: 5. Exchange code\n(+ PKCE verifier)
idp -> browser: 6. id_token +\naccess_token
browser -> apim: 7. API call\n(Bearer token)
apim -> apim: 8. validate-jwt
apim -> api: 9. Forward
api -> authz: 10. CheckPermission
authz -> api: 11. allow / deny
api -> apim: 12. Response
apim -> browser: 13. Data / 403
